WEBVTT

00:05.973 --> 00:07.908
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:07.941 --> 00:09.977
SHANE, WHAT THE FUCK HAPPENED
AT THE PARTY?

00:10.010 --> 00:12.112
I KILLED PILAR WITH
A CROQUET MALLET BY THE POOL.

00:12.145 --> 00:14.715
SHE WAS GONNA KILL US,
SO I POPPED THE BITCH.

00:17.150 --> 00:20.153
MY CHILD MURDERED SOMEONE.
I HAVE TO LEAVE TOWN NOW.

00:20.187 --> 00:22.823
YOU CAN COME IF YOU WANT.
I'D LIKE YOU TO COME.

00:22.856 --> 00:23.991
NO, I WANT TO STAY HERE

00:24.024 --> 00:26.426
AND START MY LIFE
WITH THIS WOMAN I LOVE.

00:26.460 --> 00:28.662
WELL, THAT'S NOT REALLY
AN OPTION FOR YOU ANYMORE, ANDY.

00:28.695 --> 00:30.130
WE'RE NOT GONNA WORK OUT.

00:30.163 --> 00:32.966
SO, WHAT'S
THE DESTINATION, BOSS?

00:33.000 --> 00:33.934
NORTH.

00:33.967 --> 00:36.103
TIME FOR UNCLE ANDY'S GUIDE

00:36.136 --> 00:37.938
TO LIVING OFF THE GRID.

00:37.971 --> 00:39.540
STEP ONE ‐‐
KILL YOUR OLD IDENTITY.

00:39.573 --> 00:42.442
STEP TWO ‐‐
ESTABLISHING NEW IDENTITIES.

00:42.476 --> 00:43.477
I'LL BE MIKE.

00:43.510 --> 00:45.379
SHAWN.
NATHALIE.

00:45.412 --> 00:48.081
I'LL BE "RANDY NEWMAN."
HA! N‐E‐W‐M‐A‐N.

00:48.115 --> 00:50.751
HERITAGE ‐‐ MUDDY.
JEW? AH, CAN'T TELL.

00:50.784 --> 00:53.921
THE NEWMANS WILL SUCCEED
WHERE THE BOTWINS FAILED.

00:53.954 --> 00:56.623
THEY WILL FIND JOBS,
HAVE HOBBIES.

00:56.657 --> 00:57.925
THEY WILL LIVE
A NORMAL LIFE.

00:57.958 --> 01:01.495
GO GET HER.
GET MY SON.

01:08.435 --> 01:09.903
[ LOW‐PITCHED BEEP ]

01:09.937 --> 01:12.105
[ LOW‐PITCHED BEEP ]

01:12.139 --> 01:14.007
[ HIGH‐PITCHED BEEP ]

01:16.276 --> 01:19.079
IT WAS
ABOUT FOUR MONTHS AGO,

01:19.112 --> 01:23.217
AND, UH, ANDY WAS THERE
FOR THE BIRTH, OF COURSE.

01:23.250 --> 01:26.353
AND ESTEBAN ARRIVED LATER.

01:26.386 --> 01:29.923
I PISSED OFF ANDY
LIKE YOU WOULDN'T BELIEVE.

01:29.957 --> 01:31.458
BUT I GUESS HE'S HAPPY NOW.

01:31.491 --> 01:33.861
HE TOOK OFF AFTER HER
LIKE SHE WAS MADE OF SHIT

01:33.894 --> 01:36.330
AND HE WAS KING OF THE FLIES.

01:36.363 --> 01:40.167
I HAD JUST BEEN HELD HOSTAGE,
AND MY FIANCé WAS LEAVING ME.

01:40.200 --> 01:42.035
I WASN'T ASKING
TOO MANY QUESTIONS

01:42.069 --> 01:44.538
ABOUT NANCY'S TRAVEL PLANS.

01:44.571 --> 01:46.840
FAR AWAY, I HOPE.

01:46.874 --> 01:49.743
IN MY MINIVAN.

01:49.776 --> 01:51.578
IN MY MINIVAN.

01:52.946 --> 01:56.483
[ CRYING ]

01:56.517 --> 01:58.752
Protesters: [ Chanting ]
WHAT DO WE WANT? MONEY!

01:58.785 --> 02:00.521
WHEN DO WE WANT IT?
NOW!

02:00.554 --> 02:02.623
WHAT DO WE WANT?
MONEY!

02:02.656 --> 02:03.891
WHEN DO WE WANT IT?
NOW!

02:03.924 --> 02:06.193
WHAT DO WE WANT?
MONEY!

02:06.226 --> 02:08.128
Andy: THIS IS
A REAL DILEMMA, NANCE.

02:08.161 --> 02:09.429
ON THE ONE HAND...

02:09.463 --> 02:10.597
WE WANT MONEY.

02:10.631 --> 02:12.032
WELL,
ON THE OTHER...

02:12.065 --> 02:14.067
WE WANT IT NOW?
"NEED," ACTUALLY.

02:14.101 --> 02:17.271
WE HAVE EXACTLY $793
BETWEEN US.

02:17.304 --> 02:18.906
I DON'T SEE
THE DILEMMA.

02:18.939 --> 02:21.275
WHAT DO WE WANT?
MONEY!

02:21.308 --> 02:23.177
CROSSING A PICKET LINE
IS AGAINST EVERYTHING

02:23.210 --> 02:24.945
ANDY BOTWIN'S
EVER STOOD FOR.

02:24.978 --> 02:28.615
WHAT'S BROKE‐ASS RANDY NEWMAN'S
TAKE ON IT?

02:28.649 --> 02:29.783
[ CHANTING CONTINUES ]

02:29.816 --> 02:31.451
FUCK 'EM.

02:31.485 --> 02:32.986
Stay strong.

02:33.020 --> 02:34.688
Protesters:
WHAT DO WE WANT? MONEY!

02:34.721 --> 02:37.024
Woman:
UNION BUSTERS! SCABS!

02:37.057 --> 02:39.059
WELL, YOU ALL SEEM TO HAVE
QUITE A LOT OF EXPERIENCE

02:39.092 --> 02:40.294
IN THE HOSPITALITY
INDUSTRY.

02:40.327 --> 02:42.930
WE ARE VERY PASSIONATE
ABOUT...

02:42.963 --> 02:44.298
[ Chuckling ]
HOSPITALITY.

02:45.832 --> 02:47.301
ANY PROBLEM
CROSSING THE PICKET LINE?

02:47.334 --> 02:49.937
[ Chuckling ]
OH, THEY'RE ALL BARK. NO BITE.

02:49.970 --> 02:51.171
MORALLY, I MEAN.

02:51.205 --> 02:54.875
OH, WE SYMPATHIZE
WITH BOTH SIDES.

02:54.908 --> 02:57.911
YEAH. WELL,
ONLY ONE SIDE IS RIGHT. OKAY?

02:57.945 --> 02:59.313
THOSE ARE GOOD PEOPLE
OUT THERE,

02:59.346 --> 03:01.014
AND I'D BE WITH THEM
IF I COULD.

03:01.048 --> 03:03.016
BUT I GOT TO PAY
FOR RINK TIME.

03:04.017 --> 03:05.953
UH, MY YOUNGEST
IS AN ICE DANCER.

03:05.986 --> 03:08.555
HMM.
OH!
RUSSIA, 2014.

03:08.589 --> 03:09.857
NOEL KRUSZEWSKI.

03:09.890 --> 03:10.958
REMEMBER THAT NAME.

03:10.991 --> 03:11.992
OH. NOEL KRUSZEWSKI.

03:12.025 --> 03:13.694
OH.
THAT IS SOME OUTFIT.

03:13.727 --> 03:15.629
HE'S NOT GAY.

03:15.662 --> 03:16.830
I'M SURE HE'S NOT.

03:16.864 --> 03:18.665
YEAH.
WELL, HE MIGHT BE GAY.

03:18.699 --> 03:20.200
THAT'S OKAY, TOO.

03:20.234 --> 03:22.202
SO, I'M A GREAT
PROBLEM SOLVER.

03:22.236 --> 03:24.071
I MANAGE PEOPLE
REALLY WELL.

03:24.104 --> 03:25.939
AND RANDY HERE...

03:25.973 --> 03:27.241
I DON'T TYPICALLY
TOOT MY OWN HORN,

03:27.274 --> 03:30.143
BUT I DO HAVE
EXTENSIVE CULINARY TRAINING.

03:30.177 --> 03:31.311
I AM GREAT
BEHIND THE BAR.

03:31.345 --> 03:33.313
QUICK WITH THE BOTTLE,
SHORT WITH THE POUR.

03:34.281 --> 03:36.083
WELL, THAT ALL SOUNDS
QUITE IMPRESSIVE.

03:36.850 --> 03:38.018
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:38.919 --> 03:41.088
DISHWASHER. BELLHOP. MAID.

03:46.927 --> 03:48.128
Nancy: THIS IS GOOD.

03:48.161 --> 03:49.530
IT'S GROUNDING.

03:49.563 --> 03:51.832
IT'S A...A SEEDLING

03:51.865 --> 03:54.101
FROM WHICH WE WILL BRANCH OUT
AND FLOURISH.

03:54.134 --> 03:57.838
THE NORMAL NEWMANS
FROM NORMALTOWN?

03:57.871 --> 03:59.940
AND YOU REALLY BELIEVE
WE CAN KEEP THIS UP

03:59.973 --> 04:01.808
FOR ANY SERIOUS
LENGTH OF TIME?

04:01.842 --> 04:03.977
THIS IS WHO WE ARE NOW.

04:04.011 --> 04:05.712
THIS IS US.

04:07.414 --> 04:09.917
WHAT IF YOU'D HAVE GOTTEN
A REAL JOB AFTER DAD DIED

04:09.950 --> 04:11.852
AND WE COULD HAVE SKIPPED
ALL THIS SHIT?

04:11.885 --> 04:13.921
WE WOULD HAVE
HAD TO SELL THE HOUSE.

04:13.954 --> 04:15.689
MOVE TO A VERY DIFFERENT
ZIP CODE.

04:15.722 --> 04:18.926
YOU AND SHANE WOULD HAVE GONE
TO EVEN LOUSIER PUBLIC SCHOOLS.

04:18.959 --> 04:20.494
DOESN'T SOUND SO BAD.

04:22.062 --> 04:24.064
YOU PROBABLY STILL
WOULD HAVE KNOCKED UP A GIRL.

04:24.097 --> 04:26.700
MAYBE THIS ONE WOULD HAVE
BEEN BLIND INSTEAD OF DEAF,

04:26.733 --> 04:28.235
OR MISSING A LIMB.

04:28.268 --> 04:30.204
YOU WOULD HAVE STRUGGLED
WITH YOUR GRADES,

04:30.237 --> 04:34.341
SMOKED WEED, DROPPED OUT,
GOTTEN YOUR G. E. D.

04:34.374 --> 04:36.076
YOUR BROTHER...

04:36.109 --> 04:38.612
STILL WOULD HAVE HAD
RAGE ISSUES.

04:38.645 --> 04:41.582
HE WOULD HAVE LOST HIS VIRGINITY
TO A SKANKY GIRL

04:41.615 --> 04:43.350
OR A SKANKY‐GIRL DUO.

04:43.383 --> 04:46.019
HE WOULD HAVE GROWN
INCREASINGLY ALIENATED,

04:46.053 --> 04:47.921
ENDED UP
STABBING THE MAILMAN

04:47.955 --> 04:49.056
OR MY MANAGER
AT THE GAP.

04:49.089 --> 04:51.458
WE WOULD HAVE BEEN
IN THE EXACT SAME SPOT

04:51.491 --> 04:52.593
WE'RE IN RIGHT NOW.

04:52.626 --> 04:53.927
[ BABY COOS ]

04:53.961 --> 04:55.762
SHANE.

04:55.796 --> 04:58.098
IF MOM WOULD HAVE WORKED
AT THE GAP INSTEAD
OF SELLING DRUGS,

04:58.131 --> 05:00.067
YOU THINK YOU STILL
WOULD HAVE KILLED SOMEBODY?

05:02.836 --> 05:04.605
PROBABLY.

05:09.843 --> 05:11.945
[ HORN HONKING ]

05:11.979 --> 05:13.947
[ WOMAN SHOUTING ]

05:13.981 --> 05:15.582
Andy: OH, BOY.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

05:15.616 --> 05:18.619
I THINK YOUR MOM HAS NOW
AWAKENED ALL THE HOOKERS.

05:18.652 --> 05:19.720
OKAY.

05:19.753 --> 05:21.788
UH, HOPEFULLY,
HE SHOULD SLEEP SOON.

05:21.822 --> 05:23.757
THERE'S FOUR BOTTLES
IN THE FRIDGE.

05:23.790 --> 05:25.459
CHANGING STUFF
IS ON THE DRESSER.

05:25.492 --> 05:27.494
REMEMBER TO CREAM HIS BUTT
SO HE DOESN'T GET A RASH.

05:27.528 --> 05:29.563
AND, UH, YOU GOT TO BURP HIM
EVERY TIME YOU FEED HIM.

05:29.596 --> 05:31.331
YOUR MOM'S GONNA CALL
IN A COUPLE HOURS.

05:31.365 --> 05:32.933
SHE SAYS
DON'T LEAVE THE ROOM.

05:32.966 --> 05:34.835
DID YOU REALLY JUST SAY
"CREAM HIS BUTT"?

05:34.868 --> 05:35.836
I DID.

05:35.869 --> 05:36.870
MIKE! TIME TO GO.

05:36.904 --> 05:39.773
YOU REALLY THINK
IT'S A GOOD IDEA?

05:39.806 --> 05:41.108
LEAVING PEBBLES
WITH BAMM‐BAMM?

05:41.141 --> 05:43.644
NO, BUT WE CAN'T AFFORD
CHILDCARE,

05:43.677 --> 05:46.947
SO WE HAVE TO TAKE
THIS SMALL LEAP OF FAITH.

05:46.980 --> 05:48.649
I'M ENCOURAGED,
BECAUSE SO FAR,

05:48.682 --> 05:52.085
THE BABY'S NEVER TRIED
TO HAVE US ALL KILLED.

05:52.853 --> 05:53.987
[ CHORTLES ]

05:54.021 --> 05:55.455
NICE HAT.

05:55.489 --> 05:56.823
LET'S PRACTICE.

05:56.857 --> 05:57.758
I'LL SAY "DING"
AND YOU HOP.

05:57.791 --> 05:59.560
DING!
GET ME THE REMOTE.

06:06.533 --> 06:07.467
SHIT!

06:07.501 --> 06:09.670
HE JUST TOOK THE REMOTE, STEVIE!
WE'RE SCREWED!

06:10.904 --> 06:12.139
[ SIGHS ]

06:12.172 --> 06:14.074
HEY, FUCK THIS PLACE.
LET'S ROLL.

06:16.944 --> 06:17.945
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

06:17.978 --> 06:19.513
[ THUD ]

06:34.461 --> 06:37.130
HOUSEKEEPING!

06:41.468 --> 06:42.669
HEY.

06:42.703 --> 06:44.371
HI.

06:44.404 --> 06:45.739
WHAT'S GOING ON?

06:45.772 --> 06:47.808
I FEEL LIKE
WE'RE IN A REALITY SHOW.

06:47.841 --> 06:49.810
WHO'S GETTING CHOPPED?

06:49.843 --> 06:52.479
UH, YOU THE NEW
DISHWASHER?

06:52.513 --> 06:55.015
AND‐‐ RANDY. RANDY.

06:55.048 --> 06:57.718
NOT AYN RAND‐Y. COULDN'T
GET THROUGH "ATLAS SHRUGGED."

06:57.751 --> 06:59.786
YOU START WORK
AT 11:00.

06:59.820 --> 07:01.088
YEAH.

07:01.121 --> 07:03.123
WHICH MEANS YOU NEED
TO BE HERE BEFORE 11:00

07:03.156 --> 07:04.858
SO YOU CAN BE READY
FOR INSPECTION.

07:04.892 --> 07:06.360
"INSPECTION."

07:06.393 --> 07:07.895
[ German accent ]
ARE WE READY?

07:07.928 --> 07:11.465
Together:
YES, CHEF WAGNER.

07:15.102 --> 07:16.570
MORNING, CHEF.

07:16.603 --> 07:17.738
RANDY NEWMAN.

07:17.771 --> 07:18.872
I'M A CHEF MYSELF,
YOU KNOW.

07:18.906 --> 07:20.107
SO IF THERE'S ANYTHING
I CAN DO

07:20.140 --> 07:21.575
TO HELP SPARK UP THE MENU,
PLEASE LET ME KNOW.

07:21.608 --> 07:25.579
I NOTICED THAT YOU'RE STILL
SERVING THINGS IN BREAD BOWLS.

07:25.612 --> 07:26.880
THAT IS SO '80s.

07:26.914 --> 07:28.949
SO, YOU'RE TRYING
TO BE RETRO, YEAH?

07:28.982 --> 07:30.184
WHAT ARE YOU?

07:31.185 --> 07:33.787
BIT OF AN OPEN‐ENDED
QUESTION THERE.

07:33.820 --> 07:36.356
UH, ASTROLOGICALLY,
I'M A LIBRA.

07:36.390 --> 07:39.259
SCALES ‐‐
HENCE I'M IDEALISTIC...

07:39.293 --> 07:41.528
AND ROMANTIC...
BUT ALSO A TAD IMPATIENT.

07:41.562 --> 07:43.830
HE'S THE DISHWASHER.

07:43.864 --> 07:45.499
WELL, YEAH,
AMONG OTHER THINGS,

07:45.532 --> 07:46.934
BUT TEMPORARILY.

07:46.967 --> 07:49.102
THEN I SUGGEST
YOU DO SOME DISHES.

07:49.136 --> 07:50.737
THERE AREN'T ANY
TO WASH YET.

07:50.771 --> 07:52.673
LET'S TALK FOOD!

07:55.809 --> 07:58.612
OH, I GET IT ‐‐ HAZING.
OKAY.

08:07.020 --> 08:11.692
♪♪ IT'S A CRY‐CRY‐CRYING SHAME ♪♪

08:11.725 --> 08:15.963
♪♪ THAT NO ONE EVER TOLD HER ♪♪

08:15.996 --> 08:21.935
♪♪ NOT IF YOU ALWAYS
THANK AND PLEA ♪♪

08:21.969 --> 08:26.406
♪♪ AND WON'T TOUCH MORE
THAN YOU NEED ♪♪

08:26.440 --> 08:32.246
♪♪ AND YOU MAY NEVER
REALLY KNOW ♪♪

08:32.279 --> 08:36.683
♪♪ THE JOY OF LETTING GO ♪♪

08:36.717 --> 08:41.421
[ YODELING ]

08:52.399 --> 08:53.700
[ SIGHS ]

08:58.472 --> 09:00.574
[ GRUNTING ]

09:00.607 --> 09:02.976
AND WHERE WOULD YOU LIKE IT,
MR. DUVANE?

09:03.010 --> 09:04.912
UH, YOU MAY SET IT
RIGHT ON THE BED.

09:04.945 --> 09:06.914
THANK YOU.

09:06.947 --> 09:09.516
AND CALL ME "PAUL."

09:09.550 --> 09:11.084
BEAUTIFUL ROOM!

09:11.118 --> 09:13.187
YEAH. IT'S NICE.

09:13.220 --> 09:14.254
YEAH.

09:14.288 --> 09:16.423
FANCY TV AND EVERYTHING.

09:16.456 --> 09:18.792
ALTHOUGH
I‐I DON'T REALLY WATCH TV.

09:18.825 --> 09:20.527
I LIKE BOOKS.

09:20.561 --> 09:22.829
IS THERE GONNA BE ANYTHING ELSE,
MR. DUVANE?

09:22.863 --> 09:23.830
HMM?

09:23.864 --> 09:25.599
OH, OF COURSE.
I'M SO SORRY.

09:25.632 --> 09:26.667
[ IMITATES ROBOT ]

09:26.700 --> 09:28.302
[ Robotic voice ]
RECALIBRATING FOR MANNERS.

09:28.335 --> 09:29.303
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:29.336 --> 09:31.405
[ Normal voice ]
YOU'RE IN NEED OF A REWARD.

09:31.438 --> 09:32.840
THERE WE GO.

09:32.873 --> 09:34.741
WOW.

09:34.775 --> 09:35.909
IT'S VERY GENEROUS.
THANK YOU.

09:35.943 --> 09:37.878
YEAH, WELL, YOU MUST BE TIRED.
HEAVY BAG.

09:37.911 --> 09:39.680
OH, PLEASE ‐‐
HERE. SIT.

09:39.713 --> 09:40.848
UH, I SHOULD
REALLY BE GOING.

09:40.881 --> 09:42.416
OH, NO, PLEASE.

09:52.893 --> 09:54.528
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:01.768 --> 10:03.537
[ SIGHS ]

10:03.570 --> 10:05.038
DO YOU LIKE BOOKS,
MIKE?

10:05.072 --> 10:07.975
YEAH. SURE. BOOKS ‐‐
THEY'RE ‐‐ THEY'RE OKAY.

10:08.008 --> 10:09.977
"OKAY" IS
A 60‐DEGREE DAY.

10:10.010 --> 10:11.778
WHERE'S THE HOT
AND THE COLD?

10:11.812 --> 10:14.081
I WANT YOU
TO READ TO ME.

10:15.048 --> 10:16.850
[ Chuckling ]
I'M SORRY. WHAT?

10:16.884 --> 10:19.419
YOU SEE,
I HAVE PLENTY OF BOOKS HERE,

10:19.453 --> 10:20.921
BUT THEY TIRE MY EYES.

10:20.954 --> 10:23.557
AND [SIGHS]
DON'T YOU THINK IT'S FANTASTIC

10:23.590 --> 10:27.027
WHEN YOU HEAR STORIES
IN SOMEBODY ELSE'S VOICE?

10:27.828 --> 10:30.063
I SHOULD GET...
BACK DOWNSTAIRS.

10:30.097 --> 10:31.865
THERE WAS A PREGNANT WOMAN
COMING IN ‐‐

10:31.899 --> 10:33.100
A FAMILY
OF PREG‐‐ PREGNANT WOMEN.

10:33.133 --> 10:34.334
LOTS OF BAGS.

10:34.368 --> 10:37.070
NOBODY ELSE WILL TIP YOU
AS WELL AS I WILL.

10:45.546 --> 10:48.615
SO I...I JUST SIT HERE
AND READ TO YOU?

10:48.649 --> 10:49.850
YEAH. MORE OR LESS.

10:49.883 --> 10:52.853
WHAT'S THE..."MORE"?

10:52.886 --> 10:55.022
OH. LET'S JUST FOCUS
ON THE "LESS."

11:02.329 --> 11:04.231
[ GRUNTING ]

11:10.571 --> 11:11.805
OH.

11:11.839 --> 11:14.241
PIECE OF SHIT.

11:14.274 --> 11:15.042
GOD.

11:15.075 --> 11:17.077
[ STRAINING ]

11:17.110 --> 11:19.413
YEAH, IT'S REALLY NOT WORTH IT
TO FIX IT.

11:19.446 --> 11:21.481
YOU MIGHT AS WELL
BUY A NEW ONE.
WHAT DO YOU GOT?

11:21.515 --> 11:23.684
WELL, WE EXCLUSIVELY CARRY
THE YIPPITY LINE HERE.

11:23.717 --> 11:25.819
WE GOT THE YIPPITY SPORT,
THE YIPPITY DELUXE...

11:25.853 --> 11:28.622
AND OUR BEST‐SELLER,
THE YIPPITY DRAGON.

11:28.655 --> 11:29.823
HOW MUCH IS IT?

11:29.857 --> 11:30.991
$800.

11:31.024 --> 11:33.627
FOR A STROLLER.
THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

11:33.660 --> 11:35.996
WHAT DO YOU HAVE
FOR $100?

11:36.029 --> 11:37.698
I'VE GOT
THE ‐‐ THE YIPPITY SIPPITY.

11:37.731 --> 11:38.866
THAT'S THE CUP HOLDER.

11:38.899 --> 11:41.168
A CUP HOLDER ‐‐
FOR $100?

11:41.201 --> 11:44.137
LOOK, I DON'T MAKE THE THINGS.
I JUST SELL THEM.

11:44.171 --> 11:45.272
LIVING THE DREAM.

11:45.305 --> 11:46.840
YEAH, LOOK, KID,
I BOUGHT MY HOUSE

11:46.874 --> 11:48.208
AT THE HEIGHT
OF THE MARKET,

11:48.242 --> 11:49.743
AND NOW
I'M SQUATTING IN IT.

11:49.776 --> 11:51.245
ADD TO THAT
MY SCRABBLE DEBTS

11:51.278 --> 11:53.914
AND MY WIFE WANTING ‐‐
NO, NEEDING ‐‐ THE LAP‐BAND,

11:53.947 --> 11:55.749
AND I DON'T HAVE TIME
TO DREAM.

11:55.782 --> 11:56.917
AND IF YOU AIN'T BUYING,

11:56.950 --> 11:59.753
I'M GOING BACK
TO MY ONLINE GAME.

12:07.828 --> 12:09.029
OH, GOD!

12:09.062 --> 12:10.097
I'LL COME BACK.

12:10.130 --> 12:11.498
OH, NO. WAIT.
SHE TOOK OFF.

12:11.532 --> 12:13.901
SHE SAID SHE WAS LATE
FOR HER DAY JOB.

12:13.934 --> 12:16.170
ARE ‐‐ ARE THERE KEYS
ON THE DESK?

12:17.437 --> 12:18.405
YEAH.

12:18.438 --> 12:19.806
OH, GREAT.

12:19.840 --> 12:21.508
PLEASE.
[ SIGHS ]

12:21.542 --> 12:22.643
THANK YOU.

12:26.513 --> 12:27.714
[ HANDCUFFS JINGLE ]

12:27.748 --> 12:29.650
AWKWARD.
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:29.683 --> 12:32.719
OHH. WOW.

12:32.753 --> 12:34.655
DID ‐‐ DID YOU HAVE
AN ACCIDENT?

12:34.688 --> 12:35.956
OH, NO,
THAT'S NOT MINE.

12:35.989 --> 12:37.758
HERS?

12:37.791 --> 12:38.892
YEAH.
I GOT WHAT I PAID FOR.

12:38.926 --> 12:40.360
UH, COULD YOU HURRY UP,
PLEASE?

12:40.394 --> 12:41.995
WAIT.
LET ME GET THIS STRAIGHT.

12:42.029 --> 12:44.398
SO, YOU INVITE A HOOKER
UP HERE,

12:44.431 --> 12:46.066
HAVE HER CUFF YOU
TO THE BED,

12:46.099 --> 12:47.835
DRINK A $20 BOTTLE
OF EVIAN,

12:47.868 --> 12:48.902
AND THEN PEE ON YOU.

12:48.936 --> 12:50.871
DID YOU AT ANY POINT
HAPPEN TO THINK

12:50.904 --> 12:52.372
WHO MIGHT
HAVE TO CLEAN IT UP?

12:52.406 --> 12:55.108
THAT'S YOUR JOB.
DON'T PASS JUDGMENT ON ME.

12:55.142 --> 12:57.110
I'M A PAYING GUEST!
YOU'RE THE FUCKING MAID!

12:57.144 --> 12:59.513
WILL YOU HURRY
WITH THE KEYS?!

13:02.950 --> 13:04.384
[ SCOFFS ]

13:06.086 --> 13:08.288
YOU'RE NOT EXACTLY
IN THE POWER POSITION,

13:08.322 --> 13:11.058
SO I SUGGEST YOU BE
A LITTLE MORE RESPECTFUL TO ME,

13:11.091 --> 13:13.026
THE "FUCKING MAID."

13:13.060 --> 13:14.962
I'LL LEAVE YOU
A NICE TIP, OKAY?

13:14.995 --> 13:15.896
HOW MUCH?

13:15.929 --> 13:17.164
20 BUCKS.

13:17.197 --> 13:17.798
80.

13:17.831 --> 13:19.266
OKAY, FINE.

13:22.836 --> 13:23.937
[ SIGHS ]

13:23.971 --> 13:25.639
SHE TOOK
ALL YOUR CASH...

13:25.672 --> 13:28.008
PHIL LOUNSBERRY
FROM HOBOKEN.

13:28.041 --> 13:29.076
OH, PLEASE.

13:29.109 --> 13:30.844
I'M COLD, YOU KNOW?

13:30.878 --> 13:32.813
AT FIRST, I WAS WARM...

13:32.846 --> 13:33.881
LET ME TELL YOU WHAT,
PHIL.

13:33.914 --> 13:35.282
MAY I CALL YOU PHIL?

13:35.315 --> 13:36.083
OH, YEAH.

13:36.116 --> 13:38.118
YOU WANT YOUR FREEDOM.
I WANT MINE.

13:38.151 --> 13:40.521
I'LL LEAVE SOME SHEETS FOR YOU,
RIGHT HERE.

13:40.554 --> 13:42.689
HOW ABOUT TODAY
YOU BE YOUR OWN MAID?

13:42.723 --> 13:44.358
[ SHIVERS ]
SOUND GOOD?
YEAH.

13:44.391 --> 13:45.926
DON'T WORRY
ABOUT THE TIP.

13:45.959 --> 13:48.095
[ DOOR OPENS ]

13:57.171 --> 13:59.506
I ADMIRE
YOUR SAUCE WORK.

13:59.540 --> 14:01.375
LIGHT, CLEAN,
ARTISTIC.

14:01.408 --> 14:03.010
I JUST...

14:03.043 --> 14:04.845
WE SHOULD WORK
ON A DISH TOGETHER.

14:04.878 --> 14:06.914
TELL ME ‐‐
WHERE DID YOU TRAIN?

14:06.947 --> 14:08.015
OH, GOD.

14:08.048 --> 14:10.551
MY SKILLS ARE BASED
MORE ON EXPERIENCE

14:10.584 --> 14:11.818
THAN FORMAL TRAINING.

14:11.852 --> 14:13.787
OH, FASCINATING.
YEAH.

14:13.820 --> 14:15.189
I THINK
THAT COOKING SCHOOLS

14:15.222 --> 14:16.957
CAN CRUSH
THE CREATIVE SPIRIT.

14:16.990 --> 14:18.792
MY SPIRIT IS UNCRUSHED.
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:18.825 --> 14:19.826
WHERE'D YOU LEARN
TO COOK?

14:19.860 --> 14:21.795
YOUR MOTHER'S VAGINA.

14:21.828 --> 14:24.164
REALLY?
SOUNDS VERY AVANT‐GARDE.

14:24.198 --> 14:26.633
TELL ME ‐‐
WHY ARE YOU SPEAKING TO ME?

14:26.667 --> 14:30.270
YOU ARE A DISHWASHER
WHO DOESN'T WASH DISHES.

14:30.304 --> 14:34.007
CAN YOU PLEASE TELL ME WHY
I SHOULDN'T FIRE YOU RIGHT NOW?

14:34.041 --> 14:37.344
UH, 'CAUSE MY MOTHER'S VAGINA
TAUGHT YOU HOW TO COOK.

14:37.377 --> 14:38.946
UGH!

14:38.979 --> 14:43.217
YOU WILL NEVER AGAIN
SPEAK IN MY KITCHEN.

14:43.250 --> 14:44.017
I KNOW.

14:44.051 --> 14:45.185
UNDERSTOOD?

14:45.219 --> 14:46.553
YEAH.

14:46.587 --> 14:47.754
AHH. [ SNIFFS ]

14:47.788 --> 14:49.823
It's all right.

14:49.857 --> 14:52.526
[ LIGHT PIANO MUSIC PLAYS ]

14:53.961 --> 14:56.096
COMPLIMENTS
OF THE GENTLEMAN.

15:06.974 --> 15:09.510
[ GLASSES CLINK ]

15:09.543 --> 15:12.412
LET ME GUESS ‐‐
SOMETHING IN COMPUTERS.

15:12.446 --> 15:13.847
SOFTWARE?

15:13.881 --> 15:15.549
FBI.

15:17.251 --> 15:20.521
FEDERAL BUREAU
OF INTERESTED IN <i>YOU.</i>

15:20.554 --> 15:21.855
OY.

15:21.889 --> 15:23.857
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

15:23.891 --> 15:25.092
I'M SORRY.

15:25.125 --> 15:27.094
TELLING PEOPLE I'M IN
HEATING AND AIR‐CONDITIONING

15:27.127 --> 15:29.096
ISN'T EXACTLY
AN APHRODISIAC.

15:31.732 --> 15:33.300
[ SIGHS ]

15:33.333 --> 15:34.434
I'M VINCE.

15:34.468 --> 15:36.036
OH. NATHALIE.

15:36.069 --> 15:37.938
AND WHAT DO YOU DO,
NATHALIE?

15:37.971 --> 15:38.972
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

15:39.006 --> 15:41.808
WHAT DO I DO?
EXCELLENT QUESTION.

15:41.842 --> 15:43.777
I OWN MY OWN BUSINESS.

15:43.810 --> 15:45.012
A DANCE STUDIO.

15:45.045 --> 15:47.714
MODERN DANCE.

15:47.748 --> 15:50.551
I STUDIED IN PARIS
AND...

15:50.584 --> 15:51.919
PARIS?

15:51.952 --> 15:54.922
C'EST UNE VILLE
TRES JOLIE.

15:54.955 --> 15:57.858
OUI.
PRESQUE PARFAITE.

15:57.891 --> 15:58.759
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

15:58.792 --> 15:59.760
WHERE WERE YOU?

15:59.793 --> 16:01.562
THE NEUVE ARRONDISEMENT.

16:03.964 --> 16:05.432
IT WAS GREAT.

16:05.465 --> 16:08.168
IT WAS SO GREAT.

16:08.202 --> 16:09.169
UM...

16:09.203 --> 16:10.671
BUT THEN NEW YORK BECKONED
AND...

16:10.704 --> 16:11.839
AND SEATTLE?

16:11.872 --> 16:13.640
YEAH.

16:13.674 --> 16:15.475
MM.

16:15.509 --> 16:16.343
I GET RESTLESS.

16:16.376 --> 16:18.445
AND THIS OPPORTUNITY
CAME ALONG ‐‐

16:18.478 --> 16:19.813
MY OWN BUSINESS.

16:19.847 --> 16:21.915
NO ONE LOOKING
OVER MY SHOULDER.

16:21.949 --> 16:22.916
YOU KNOW?

16:22.950 --> 16:24.852
KIDS?
YEAH. UH, WHAT?

16:24.885 --> 16:26.320
KIDS?
UH...NO.

16:26.353 --> 16:27.754
MNH‐MNH. NO.

16:27.788 --> 16:29.790
HUSBAND?
BOYFRIEND?

16:29.823 --> 16:31.825
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:31.859 --> 16:34.661
I HAVE A...A HISTORY

16:34.695 --> 16:39.666
OF KILLING ANYTHING
THAT COULD CONCEIVABLY WORK OUT.

16:39.700 --> 16:41.835
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:41.869 --> 16:43.637
WELL...

16:43.670 --> 16:46.840
NOT EVERYTHING IS MEANT
TO HAVE A LONG SHELF LIFE.

16:46.874 --> 16:48.008
YEAH.

16:48.041 --> 16:49.810
YOU GOT TO PICK THE FRUIT
WHILE IT'S RIPE.

16:49.843 --> 16:50.844
I LOVE FRUIT.

16:50.878 --> 16:51.912
Don:
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

16:51.945 --> 16:53.247
UNH‐UNH.

16:53.280 --> 16:54.915
EXCUSE ME, SIR.
DON KRUSZEWSKI.

16:54.948 --> 16:56.250
HOTEL MANAGER.

16:56.283 --> 16:58.519
I JUST NEED A QUICK WORD
WITH MY EMPLOYEE HERE. OKAY?

16:58.552 --> 17:00.454
COME. OVER HERE.

17:02.222 --> 17:03.624
OKAY.

17:03.657 --> 17:05.225
FIRST OFF, GIVE ME THAT.
OKAY?

17:05.259 --> 17:07.928
THE WIG ISN'T
FOOLING ANYONE, OKAY?

17:07.961 --> 17:09.162
NO STAFF AT THE BAR.

17:09.196 --> 17:10.898
I DON'T CARE IF YOU'RE OFF
THE CLOCK ‐‐ LOOK AT ME.

17:10.931 --> 17:12.432
GO AND DRINK
DOWN THE STREET. OKAY?

17:12.466 --> 17:13.333
SECOND, GUESS WHAT.

17:13.367 --> 17:14.635
YOU'RE NOT
OFF THE CLOCK YET. OKAY?

17:14.668 --> 17:16.803
'CAUSE ONE OF OUR VALUED
REGULARS, MR. LOUNSBERRY,

17:16.837 --> 17:18.038
HE JUST CALLED
HOUSEKEEPING

17:18.071 --> 17:19.773
TO SAY THAT HIS SHEETS
HAD NOT BEEN CHANGED

17:19.806 --> 17:21.108
AND HIS BED
HAD NOT BEEN MADE.

17:21.141 --> 17:25.012
GET UP TO 612 IMMEDIATELY
AND DO YOUR JOB. HUH?

17:25.045 --> 17:27.314
WHILE YOU STILL HAVE IT.

17:28.782 --> 17:31.051
HOPE YOU'RE ENJOYING
YOUR STAY.

17:35.956 --> 17:36.857
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:36.890 --> 17:38.725
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

17:55.776 --> 17:59.713
"DEAR MAID, YOU KNOW I LOVE
PAYING WOMEN FOR DIRTY JOBS.

17:59.746 --> 18:01.715
THANKS."

18:18.899 --> 18:22.302
HE'S GONNA PAY YOU
TO READ TO HIM?

18:22.336 --> 18:23.370
YEAH.

18:23.403 --> 18:26.406
I'M SUPPOSED TO SIT IN HIS ROOM
AND READ TO HIM...

18:26.440 --> 18:27.708
IN MY UNDERWEAR.

18:27.741 --> 18:28.709
OH.

18:28.742 --> 18:29.643
HOW MUCH?

18:29.676 --> 18:30.944
50 BUCKS A PAGE.

18:30.978 --> 18:32.946
OH, NOT BAD!

18:32.980 --> 18:36.083
I ONCE ATE ANGELO COSTELLO'S
BOOGERS FOR 25 CENTS.

18:36.116 --> 18:37.317
THAT'S DISGUSTING.

18:37.351 --> 18:38.385
YEAH. EXACTLY.

18:38.418 --> 18:40.787
TAKE OFF YOUR PANTS.
GO READ TO THIS OLD WEIRDO.

18:40.821 --> 18:42.122
WEAR BOXERS ‐‐

18:42.155 --> 18:43.991
PREFERABLY ONES
THAT DON'T GAPE.

18:44.024 --> 18:47.060
READ FAST,
AND, UH, SKIP PARAGRAPHS.

18:47.094 --> 18:48.795
IT'S NOT GAY, RIGHT?

18:48.829 --> 18:50.163
NOT IF HE PAYS YOU.

18:50.197 --> 18:52.833
OR IF IT'S UNDERWATER.

18:52.866 --> 18:54.168
[ SCOFFS ]

18:54.201 --> 18:55.536
THIS FUCKING SUCKS.

18:55.569 --> 18:57.871
YOU NEVER KNOW.
MIGHT BE A TERRIFIC BOOK.

18:57.905 --> 18:59.506
YOU'LL GET LOST
IN THE NARRATIVE.

18:59.540 --> 19:01.775
OH, BOY. I NEVER THOUGHT
I'D BE WASHING DISHES AGAIN.

19:01.808 --> 19:05.179
AND WHO PUTS TROUT ALMONDINE
ON A FUCKING MENU ANYMORE?

19:05.212 --> 19:08.649
IT'S LIKE HE'S COOKING
FOR THE RESISTANCE.

19:08.682 --> 19:09.516
YOU MISSED A SPOT.

19:09.550 --> 19:12.019
BACK OFF, READING RAINBOW.
[ SIGHS ]

19:12.052 --> 19:13.887
[ SIGHS ]

19:13.921 --> 19:15.055
HEY!

19:15.088 --> 19:16.490
HOW WAS YOUR DAY, NAT?

19:16.523 --> 19:21.495
UH...I'M NO BETTER THAN
THE WHORE WHO PEES ON PEOPLE.

19:21.528 --> 19:22.896
OH.

19:22.930 --> 19:26.200
SILAS, I THINK
MOMMY HAS A STORY, TOO.

19:29.503 --> 19:31.972
I NEED SOMETHING
STRONGER THAN <i>THIS.</i>

19:32.005 --> 19:33.841
[ SIGHS ]

19:33.874 --> 19:35.609
HEY, BUDDY.
YOU'RE THE PIANO PLAYER, RIGHT?

19:35.642 --> 19:38.145
I LIKE WHAT YOU DID WITH
"SHE'S ALWAYS A WOMAN" IN THERE.

19:38.178 --> 19:39.813
OH, THANK YOU, MAN.
THANK YOU.

19:39.847 --> 19:40.914
HEY, YOU SHOULD HEAR

19:40.948 --> 19:42.783
MY "SCENES
FROM AN ITALIAN RESTAURANT."

19:42.816 --> 19:44.785
LOOKING FORWARD TO IT.
YEAH.

19:44.818 --> 19:46.587
SO, UH...

19:46.620 --> 19:48.922
YOU KNOW WHERE I COULD SCORE
SOME WEED AROUND HERE?

19:48.956 --> 19:51.124
YOU'RE SHIT OUT OF LUCK
ON THAT ONE, MAN.

19:51.158 --> 19:53.594
NIGEL THE VALET USED TO SUPPLY,
BUT HE'S ON STRIKE.

19:53.627 --> 19:56.029
AND THE MOTHERFUCKER
WON'T SELL TO NOBODY

19:56.063 --> 19:57.865
WHO CROSSES
THE PICKET LINE.

19:57.898 --> 20:00.601
THANKS. HERE.
HAVE A‐A MINI‐FRANGELICO.

20:00.634 --> 20:02.970
OH.

20:04.838 --> 20:06.340
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

20:06.373 --> 20:07.708
Nancy: WHAT?

20:07.741 --> 20:09.309
NO, NO!

20:09.343 --> 20:11.011
I'M NOT THINKING
ANYTHING.

20:12.312 --> 20:14.248
I'M NOT. I'M A MAID.
I LOVE MY JOB.

20:14.281 --> 20:17.718
I LEAVE THINGS CLEAN
AND IN ORDER.

20:17.751 --> 20:20.120
WE'RE THE NEWMANS.

20:20.153 --> 20:22.489
IT'S A WHOLE NEW LIFE.

20:26.960 --> 20:29.062
WELL...I MUST SAY,

20:29.096 --> 20:31.999
YOU LOOK PRETTY GOOD
FOR HAVING CANCER.

20:32.032 --> 20:34.868
WELL, THEY HAVEN'T STARTED
THE CHEMO YET,

20:34.902 --> 20:37.638
SO MOSTLY
I'M JUST KIND OF...BLAH.

20:37.671 --> 20:39.907
BUT, UM,
SO, TO BE CLEAR,

20:39.940 --> 20:42.843
YOU DON'T DISPENSE
ANY MARIJUANA HERE AT ALL?

20:42.876 --> 20:45.879
ALL WE ARE
IS A PATIENT NETWORK.

20:45.913 --> 20:47.714
WE CONNECT YOU
WITH A CAREGIVER ‐‐

20:47.748 --> 20:48.849
GROWER.

20:48.882 --> 20:50.250
AND THEN YOU MAKE
YOUR OWN ARRANGEMENTS

20:50.284 --> 20:52.452
FOR THE MEDICINE ‐‐
MARIJUANA.

20:52.486 --> 20:53.587
GREAT.
LET'S NETWORK.

20:53.620 --> 20:56.857
AS SOON AS I SEE
YOUR DOCTOR'S AUTHORIZATION.

20:56.890 --> 20:59.092
OKAY.
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

20:59.126 --> 21:02.729
HE'S NOT IN THE STRICTEST SENSE
OF THE WORD A DOCTOR.

21:02.763 --> 21:06.033
IT'S A MORE...
ALTERNATIVE TREATMENT.

21:06.066 --> 21:07.801
EXPERIMENTAL STUFF.

21:07.835 --> 21:09.136
RULES, DEAR.

21:09.169 --> 21:11.705
IF I DON'T SEE THE CONSENT
SIGNED BY A PHYSICIAN

21:11.738 --> 21:13.707
LICENSED
IN THIS STATE...

21:13.740 --> 21:14.875
[ GASPS ]

21:14.908 --> 21:15.843
THERE IT IS.

21:15.876 --> 21:17.544
WHAT?

21:17.578 --> 21:19.346
IN YOUR SHOES.

21:21.248 --> 21:23.383
THOSE LOOK LIKE MY SIZE.

21:23.417 --> 21:24.885
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

21:24.918 --> 21:26.753
I REALLY LIKE SHOES.

21:34.828 --> 21:37.097
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

21:38.632 --> 21:40.367
[ CHAIN RATTLES ]

21:41.468 --> 21:42.836
HELLO.

21:42.870 --> 21:44.571
HI.
DOLORES SENT ME.

21:44.605 --> 21:45.939
NATHALIE.

21:45.973 --> 21:47.641
COME IN.

21:51.345 --> 21:54.748
FIONA!
THE SEITAN IS BURNING!

21:55.816 --> 21:58.051
AND SAVE THE OIL!

21:58.085 --> 21:59.486
FUELS OUR VAN.

21:59.520 --> 22:03.891
PAIN IN THE ASS TO COLLECT,
BUT GAIA THANKS US.

22:03.924 --> 22:06.059
GO GREEN.

22:06.093 --> 22:07.661
YOU GOT CASH?

22:12.299 --> 22:15.035
UM...I'M THINKING
THIS IS A DOWN PAYMENT...

22:15.068 --> 22:17.838
WITH A LITTLE MORE PRODUCT...
ON CONSIGNMENT?

22:17.871 --> 22:20.874
HERE, YOU GET
WHAT YOU PAY FOR.

22:20.908 --> 22:22.910
PLEASE?

22:22.943 --> 22:25.746
AS ONE SISTER TO ANOTHER?

22:25.779 --> 22:27.648
I'M REALLY GOOD
AT MOVING PRODUCT.

22:27.681 --> 22:29.483
I COULD BE
YOUR BIGGEST CUSTOMER.

22:29.516 --> 22:30.651
HM.

22:30.684 --> 22:33.187
EXCEPT YOU'RE NOT MY SISTER,
AND WE'RE NOT WHOLESALERS.

22:33.220 --> 22:36.123
WE SELL
FOR PERSONAL USE ONLY.

22:46.166 --> 22:48.302
OH. YOU DON'T KEEP
YOUR TRIMMINGS.

22:48.335 --> 22:50.370
AH. WE USED TO USE THEM
FOR COMPOST.

22:50.404 --> 22:52.906
TURNS OUT THEY ARE BAD
FOR THE BEETROOT...

22:52.940 --> 22:54.575
OR ANYONE
WHO EATS THE BEETROOT, SO...

22:54.608 --> 22:55.576
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

22:55.609 --> 22:57.077
[ IMITATING AIRPLANE NOISES ]

23:00.447 --> 23:02.416
[ Chuckling ] AW.

23:02.449 --> 23:03.851
SHE'S CUTE.

23:03.884 --> 23:05.385
HOW OLD IS SHE?

23:05.419 --> 23:06.320
HE IS 5.

23:06.353 --> 23:09.823
KISH, YOU BETTER BE SHOOTING
PEACE RAYS.

23:09.857 --> 23:12.059
I TOLD YOU ‐‐
WE NEED TO CUT HIS HAIR.

23:12.092 --> 23:13.594
HEY, HE'S GOOD.

23:13.627 --> 23:15.028
YOU'RE GONNA MAKE HIM
A FAG!

23:15.062 --> 23:16.496
Fiona: OHH.

23:16.530 --> 23:18.365
Nancy: BOYS CAN BE
REALLY VIOLENT.

23:18.398 --> 23:20.400
IT'S ALL
KILL, KILL...KILL.

23:20.434 --> 23:21.301
KISH...

23:21.335 --> 23:23.670
GO INTO
THE CONTEMPLATION CORNER.

23:23.704 --> 23:25.873
[ STOMPING ]

23:25.906 --> 23:27.474
Fiona:
[ Chuckling ] OKAY.

23:27.508 --> 23:30.477
SO, YOUR TRIMMINGS, YOU JUST ‐‐
YOU THROW THEM AWAY?

23:30.511 --> 23:32.312
WELL, IF WE EVER
GET OUR CERTIFICATE

23:32.346 --> 23:33.780
FROM THE HEALTH
DEPARTMENT,

23:33.814 --> 23:35.516
WE ARE THINKING
OF MAKING EDIBLES.

23:35.549 --> 23:38.685
UH, HEALTH DEPARTMENT ‐‐
NOTORIOUS FEET‐DRAGGERS.

23:38.719 --> 23:40.487
COULD TAKE YEARS.

23:40.521 --> 23:41.555
I'LL TAKE THEM.

23:41.588 --> 23:44.358
DOESN'T MEAN
WE'RE GIVING THEM AWAY.

23:44.391 --> 23:47.628
I'M THINKING $100
BUYS ME A LOT OF TRIMMINGS.

23:47.661 --> 23:48.695
[ SIGHS ]

23:50.864 --> 23:52.466
[ SLURPS ]

23:55.636 --> 23:57.337
[ BABY COOS ]

23:57.371 --> 23:59.206
YIPPITY‐KI‐YAY, MOTHERFUCKER.

24:00.774 --> 24:04.578
♪♪ I'M HAPPY AS CAN BE ♪♪

24:04.611 --> 24:07.381
♪♪ SO HAPPY BEING ME ♪♪

24:09.917 --> 24:13.554
♪♪ EVERYTHING IS GOING MY WAY ♪♪

24:13.587 --> 24:16.557
♪♪ SO LISTEN TO ME SAY ♪♪

24:16.590 --> 24:17.791
♪♪ I'M HAPPY AS CAN BE ♪♪

24:17.824 --> 24:21.428
♪♪ HAPPY, HAPPY ♪♪

24:21.461 --> 24:23.931
♪♪ THE SUN IS SHINING
IN THE SKY ♪♪

24:23.964 --> 24:26.133
♪♪ SUN IS SHINING ♪♪

24:26.166 --> 24:27.935
♪♪ I EAT A PIECE OF APPLE PIE ♪♪

24:27.968 --> 24:30.070
♪♪ APPLE PIE, APPLE PIE ♪♪

24:30.103 --> 24:33.874
♪♪ TAKE MY HAND
AND WALK WITH ME ♪♪

24:33.907 --> 24:37.744
♪♪ THERE'S SO MUCH BEAUTY
HERE TO SEE ♪♪

24:37.778 --> 24:39.980
♪♪ SHINING ♪♪

24:42.416 --> 24:43.717
[ RATTLING ]

24:43.750 --> 24:47.087
Silas: "IF YOU WANT TO SEE
THE INSIDE OF THE SPACESHIP,

24:47.120 --> 24:49.156
"GO TO PAGE 64.

24:49.189 --> 24:51.625
"IF YOU DECIDE
TO STAY IN THE FOREST,

24:51.658 --> 24:53.794
GO TO...PAGE 114."

24:53.827 --> 24:55.429
GO INSIDE.
GO INSIDE.

24:59.633 --> 25:03.937
"YOUR MOVE HAS PAID OFF.
THEY WELCOME YOU IN FOR A MEAL.

25:03.971 --> 25:05.672
YOU NEVER DIE."

25:05.706 --> 25:06.707
I NEVER WHAT?

25:06.740 --> 25:10.677
♪♪ I'M HAPPY AS CAN BE ♪♪

25:10.711 --> 25:13.647
♪♪ HAPPY BEING ME ♪♪

25:20.988 --> 25:24.291
I THOUGHT THE NEWMANS
WERE DOING THINGS DIFFERENTLY.

25:24.324 --> 25:25.158
WE ARE.

25:26.426 --> 25:28.028
WE'RE MAKING HASH.

